     <div type="poem">
   <head>¶Maister doctor Byll.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>Images are made to put vs in mynde</l>
      <l>Of that which is dead or farre absent,</l>
      <l>But God is neither as we do fynde.</l>
      <l>But aye liuing, and eche where present.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Images are cursed grauen by mans wyt</l>
      <l>In place that are set for any religion,</l>
      <l>But an Image made out of holy wryt,</l>
      <l>Is not forbidden in myne opinion.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>An Image is painted here in this boke,</l>
      <l>Neither with false <gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 word">
            <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
         </gap>, nor mās inuētiōs</l>
      <l>But out of Gods boke set out to all folke,</l>
      <l>Fruitfull &amp; necessary to al true christiās</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Hutchinson shope it for good men to regard</l>
      <l>With thankes his costes, with prayse his paynes rewarde.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
